translated: Jeansson, John Birger, cavalry captain, director, Kalmar, b. 27/7/94 in Kalmar to consular John J. and Sigrid Maijström. Married on 21/xx to Henrietta Norberg. Children: Märtha b. 26, Lars-Johan b. 33. Education: High school examination 12, reserve officer examination 14, DHS (unknown abbreviation) 17, business studies in North and South America 18-19. Lieutenant in Småland's hussar regiment reserve 14, lieutenant 18, cavalry captain in Livregementets husarer reserve 29. Executive director of Ångbåts A-B Kalmarsund since 20 and previous executive director of Kalmar Ängkvarns K-B. Member of the city council 30, chairman 33, vice chairman 34-38, member of the finance committee 24-38, chairman of the fire board 28-40, member of the county administrative board 30-37, chairman of the Swedish Handelsbanken local committee since 36, vice chairman of the Småland and Blekinge Chamber of Commerce since 42, member of the board for the General Fire Insurance Company of the Cities since 44, vice chairman of the Swedish Milling Profession Association since 36. Awarded RVO (Royal Order of Vasa) in 36, RFinlVROlkl (unknown abbreviation).
